The paper discusses the generation of adversarial examples using deep learning architectures, which falls under the categories of machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the perturbation analysis of these architectures, which falls under the category of cryptography and security (cs.CR). Finally, the paper proposes new algorithms for generating adversarial examples, which falls under the category of neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE).
